    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ee415897_0d092312",
        "filename": "milo/buildsource/buildbucket/builder.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 207,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-04T17:32:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "that would be really cool, it would allow implementing https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circuit_breaker per host, but that\u0027s outside of the scope. My concern is that there should be *some* bound. I believe, number of concurrent requests handled by a single instance is bound too, so if we put a bound here, there is still a limit (albeit a large one). My concern specifically is that we may go out of file descriptors for outgoing network connections. Ideally there is a semaphore for any system resource.\n\nimplementing a per-instance limit shouldn\u0027t hard. We already have our own transport. If we do that, then FanOutIn here is fine",
